<span id="v.xv-p159"></span> *In concilio Nicœni tractatus*—“the Council
of the Nicene tractate or creed,” possibly. The reference is plain,
though there are various readings, and *tractatus* may not mean the
creed. The real difficulty is that in the 20 extant Canons of Nicæa,
there is no reference of the kind, and there is no evidence that any are
missing. Perhaps St. Ambrose is quoting from memory, or some faulty
collection, and so other canons are wrongly spoken of as Nicene. On the
subject comp. St. Ambr. *de Off.* I. 257, and *Dict. Chr. Ant.* art.
“Digamy.”

