<span id="v.xv-p270"></span> The expression “*Aula regalisi*” applied to
the Blessed Virgin is also used by St. Ambrose, *de Inst. Virg.* XII.
79, and in the Hymn for the Nativity of our Lord—“*Veni Redemptor
gentium,*” verse 4—“*Procedit e thalamo Suo, Pudoris aula Regia.*” The
force is lost in the translation adopted in *Hymns Ancient and Modern,*
No. 57, but is preserved in Dr. Neale’s version, “Proceeding from His
chamber free, The royal hall of chastity.”—*Hymnal Noted,* No. 31.

